ProtoDefines:
. "A \term{periodic continued fraction} is a continued fraction
   $[a_0, a_1, \ldots, a_n, \ldots]$ such that $$ a_n = a_{n+h}
   $$ for some fixed positive integer $h$ and all sufficiently 
   large $n$. We call the minimal such $h$ the \term{ period of 
   the continued fraction} ."
